{
  "$schema_note": "Seed data for the `role_skill_requirements` table. Each role lists 10-13 skill requirements with required_level (1-5), importance (REQUIRED|PREFERRED|NICE_TO_HAVE), and weight (sum ~= 1.00 within each role for weighted composite scoring).",
  "version": "pilot-v1",
  "created_at": "2026-05-26",
  "scoring_notes": "SkillDiffService.computeMatchScore() uses these weights. For each requirement: match_strength = 1.0 (cv_level >= required_level), or (cv_level / required_level) if cv_level < required_level (partial), or 0 (missing). Final score = SUM(weight × match_strength) / SUM(weight) × 100.",
  "design_notes": "Importance is a SEMANTIC label for UI display. Weight is what drives the math. REQUIRED skills carry the heaviest weights (0.08-0.20). PREFERRED 0.05-0.10. NICE_TO_HAVE 0.02-0.05. Soft skills (communication etc.) have low weight individually but appear across all roles.",
  "validation_rules": [
    "Each role must have at least 8 skills (otherwise scoring is too coarse).",
    "Sum of weights per role should be 0.95 <= sum <= 1.05 (small rounding tolerance).",
    "Every skill_id referenced here must exist in skills-pilot.json (by canonical_name).",
    "required_level must be 1-5 (matches user_skills.level convention)."
  ],
